{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871898546,"sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a36b38a001gI6Ga4sCvFhWlM","messageID":"msg_d7a369964001EEkf7DszIKIOZR","sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bb157260ae654f3ab4a990ae1df59435","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal describes the design and implementation of `DockerService` as a core service module within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### DockerService Class (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n10: \n11: The `DockerService` class will encapsulate all Docker SDK interactions:\n12: \n13: - **Docker availability check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n14: - **Image building**: Build container images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments\n15: - **Image information retrieval**: Query image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n16: - **Image pushing**: Authenticate and push images to container registries\n17: - **Image removal**: Clean up local images with graceful error handling\n18: \n19: **Class interface**:\n20: ```python\n21: class DockerService:\n22:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n23:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool\n24:     def build_image(\n25:         self,\n26:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n27:         context_path: Path,\n28:         image_name: str,\n29:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n30:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n31:     ) -> Dict[str, str]\n32:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]\n33:     def push_image(\n34:         self,\n35:         image_name: str,\n36:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n37:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n38:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n39:     ) -> Dict[str, str]\n40:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### Method Responsibilities\n44: \n45: #### `check_docker_available()`\n46: - Attempts to connect to Docker daemon via `docker.from_env()`\n47: - Returns `True` if connection succeeds, `False` otherwise\n48: - Logs warnings when Docker is unavailable (respecting `verbose` flag)\n49: \n50: #### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)`\n51: - Builds image using `client.images.build()`\n52: - Streams build logs to CLI for real-time user feedback\n53: - Supports build arguments for proxy configuration\n54: - Tags image as `{image_name}:{tag}`\n55: - Returns dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n56: - Raises `RuntimeError` on build failure\n57: \n58: #### `get_image_info(image_name)`\n59: - Retrieves image metadata via `client.images.get()`\n60: - Returns dict with `id`, `repo_tags`, `size`, `created`\n61: - Uses internal `_format_size()` for human-readable size formatting\n62: - Raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` if image doesn't exist\n63: \n64: #### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n65: - Logs in to registry if credentials provided via `_docker_login_sdk()`\n66: - Retags image if `registry_url` is specified via `_tag_image_sdk()`\n67: - Streams push logs to CLI\n68: - Returns dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n69: - Handles authentication errors gracefully\n70: \n71: #### `remove_image(image_name)`\n72: - Removes image via `client.images.remove()`\n73: - Returns `True` on success\n74: - Logs warning and returns `False` on failure\n75: - Forces removal if image has dependent containers\n76: \n77: ## Design Considerations\n78: \n79: ### Error Handling Strategy\n80: - Wrap Docker SDK exceptions with descriptive error messages\n81: - Maintain stack traces in verbose mode for debugging\n82: - Use `RuntimeError` for unrecoverable failures (Docker unavailable, build failures)\n83: - Log warnings for non-critical issues (image removal failures)\n84: \n85: ### Logging and Verbosity\n86: - Respect `verbose` flag for detailed operation logging\n87: - Use Python standard `logging` module\n88: - Log at INFO level for normal operations, DEBUG for verbose mode\n89: - Integration with CLI's verbose flag passed from runtime classes\n90: \n91: ### Streaming Output\n92: - Stream build and push logs to CLI using generators\n93: - Provide real-time feedback to users during long-running operations\n94: - Decode Docker API log lines for display\n95: \n96: ### Registry Authentication\n97: - Support standard Docker registry authentication\n98: - Handle both Docker Hub and private registries\n99: - Store credentials securely via Docker SDK (not in code)\n100: - Support `registry_url` parameter for non-Docker-Hub registries\n101: \n102: ## Integration Points\n103: \n104: ### BuildRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n105: - Uses `build_image()` for local Docker builds\n106: - Uses `get_image_info()` after build to retrieve image metadata\n107: - Uses `remove_image()` for cleanup on build failure\n108: \n109: ### PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n110: - Uses `push_image()` for publishing to registries\n111: - Uses `get_image_info()` for image metadata display\n112: - Passes registry credentials from metadata to push operation\n113: \n114: ### CLI Commands\n115: - Indirect usage via runtime classes (no direct CLI integration)\n116: - Errors propagated through runtime error handling\n117: - Verbose flag passed from CLI commands through runtimes\n118: \n119: ## Impact Analysis\n120: \n121: ### Positive Impacts\n122: \n123: 1. **Separation of concerns**: Docker operations isolated from business logic\n124: 2. **Testability**: Easy to mock Docker SDK for unit testing\n125: 3. **Maintainability**: Single source of truth for Docker operations\n126: 4. **Reusability**: Consistent Docker behavior across CLI commands\n127: 5. **Error handling**: Centralized, consistent error messages\n128: \n129: ### Breaking Changes\n130: \n131: None. This is a new service module that doesn't modify existing functionality.\n132: \n133: ### Dependencies\n134: \n135: - **New dependency**: `docker>=6.0.0` (Docker SDK for Python)\n136: - **Existing dependencies**: `pathlib`, `logging`, `typing`, `rich` (for logging integration)\n137: \n138: ### File Modifications\n139: \n140: 1. **New file**:\n141:    - `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`: Complete `DockerService` implementation\n142: \n143: 2. **Modified files**:\n144:    - `agentcube/services/__init__.py`: Add service docstring\n145:    - `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` instead of direct SDK calls\n146:    - `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` for push operations\n147: \n148: 3. **Configuration**:\n149:    - `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`: Add `docker>=6.0.0` to project dependencies\n150: \n151: ### Risk Assessment\n152: \n153: | Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n154: |------|------------|------------|\n155: | Docker SDK API changes | Low | Pin version to `docker>=6.0.0,<7.0.0` |\n156: | Registry authentication failures | Medium | Comprehensive error messages, retry logic |\n157: | Build log streaming issues | Low | Test with various Dockerfile scenarios |\n158: | Proxy build_args handling | Medium | Validate build_args format before use |\n159: \n160: ## Alternatives Considered\n161: \n162: ### Alternative 1: Direct Docker CLI integration\n163: \n164: **Approach**: Use `subprocess` to call `docker build`, `docker push`, etc.\n165: \n166: **Rejected because**:\n167: - Requires parsing CLI output instead of structured data\n168: - Less portable across operating systems\n169: - No native Python error handling\n170: - Harder to test\n171: \n172: ### Alternative 2: No abstraction layer\n173: \n174: **Approach**: Directly import and use Docker SDK in runtime classes\n175: \n176: **Rejected because**:\n177: - Duplicates Docker initialization logic\n178: - Inconsistent error handling across runtimes\n179: - Harder to mock for testing\n180: - Mixes concerns (Docker operations vs agent lifecycle)\n181: \n182: ### Alternative 3: Third-party Docker wrapper\n183: \n184: **Approach**: Use existing Docker wrapper libraries\n185: \n186: **Rejected because**:\n187: - Adds unnecessary dependency\n188: - Existing libraries may not match CLI requirements\n189: - Custom implementation allows tighter integration with CLI features\n190: \n191: ## Acceptance Criteria\n192: \n193: ### Core Functionality\n194: \n195: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when Docker daemon is running\n196: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` when Docker daemon is stopped\n197: - [ ] `build_image()` successfully builds images from Dockerfiles\n198: - [ ] `build_image()` streams build logs to console\n199: - [ ] `build_image()` supports build_args for proxy configuration\n200: - [ ] `get_image_info()` returns correct image metadata\n201: - [ ] `get_image_info()` formats size in human-readable format\n202: - [ ] `push_image()` successfully pushes to Docker Hub with credentials\n203: - [ ] `push_image()` handles registry URL retagging\n204: - [ ] `remove_image()` removes images successfully\n205: - [ ] `remove_image()` returns `False` on failure and logs warning\n206: \n207: ### Error Handling\n208: \n209: - [ ] Raises `RuntimeError` when Docker is unavailable\n210: - [ ] Raises appropriate exceptions for build failures\n211: - [ ] Handles authentication failures gracefully\n212: - [ ] Logs detailed errors in verbose mode\n213: - [ ] Provides user-friendly error messages\n214: \n215: ### Integration\n216: \n217: - [ ] BuildRuntime successfully uses DockerService for local builds\n218: - [ ] PublishRuntime successfully uses DockerService for publishing\n219: - [ ] Verbose flag is respected for logging\n220: - [ ] Errors propagate correctly through runtime classes\n221: \n222: ### Testing\n223: \n224: - [ ] Unit tests for all public methods\n225: - [ ] Mock Docker SDK for testing without Docker daemon\n226: - [ ] Integration tests with real Docker daemon\n227: - [ ] Test proxy configuration via build_args\n228: - [ ] Test registry authentication and push\n229: \n230: ## Implementation Timeline\n231: \n232: Estimated effort: **3-4 days**\n233: \n234: | Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n235: |-------|----------|--------------|\n236: | Phase 1: Core implementation | 1.5 days | `DockerService` class with all methods |\n237: | Phase 2: Error handling and logging | 0.5 day | Comprehensive error handling, verbose logging |\n238: | Phase 3: Runtime integration | 0.5 day | Update BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime |\n239: | Phase 4: Testing | 1 day | Unit tests, integration tests |\n240: | Phase 5: Documentation | 0.5 day | Docstrings, examples, pyproject.toml update |\n241: \n242: ## References\n243: \n244: - CLI Toolkit Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` (lines 216-243)\n245: - CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` (Requirements 547-563 for Docker integration)\n246: - Docker SDK Documentation: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n247: - BuildRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n248: - PublishRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n(End of file - total 248 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal describes the design and implementation of `DockerService` as a core service module within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n\n## Scope\n\n### DockerService Class (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n\nThe `DockerService` class will encapsulate all Docker SDK interactions:\n\n- **Docker availability check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n- **Image building**: Build container images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments\n- **Image information retrieval**: Query image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n- **Image pushing**: Authenticate and push images to container registries\n- **Image removal**: Clean up local images with graceful error handling\n\n**Class interface**:\n```python","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871898524,"end":1775871898542}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775871898573,"sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a36b3b1001D0Y2tC8mDGKdeo","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a369964001EEkf7DszIKIOZR","sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":39081,"input":23967,"output":75,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775871900345,"sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a36bab6001uAb5CLSkt063rw","messageID":"msg_d7a36b3e4001tERcoLgP883kBM","sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871996063,"sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a382f84001urxWjk3jBecM2p","messageID":"msg_d7a36b3e4001tERcoLgP883kBM","sessionID":"ses_285caf619ffesRAlW2MSoicCcL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7bc88557824c49c08e4c3aed7137fb98","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型增强\n\n## 概述\n\n本文档针对 AgentCube CLI 项目中的 MetadataService 和数据模型进行架构增强提案。该提案旨在改进元数据管理、验证机制、数据模型的扩展性以及与 Kubernetes CRD 的集成能力。\n\n## 背景\n\n当前 AgentCube CLI 项目已经实现了基础的元数据管理功能，包括：\n\n- `AgentMetadata` Pydantic 模型（包含20+字段）\n- `MetadataService` 用于加载、保存和验证元数据\n- 支持 YAML 格式的元数据持久化\n- 与 Kubernetes AgentRuntime CRD 的集成\n\n然而，在代码审查和实际使用中发现了一些需要改进的方面：\n\n1. **数据验证不够完善**：部分字段的验证逻辑分散，缺乏统一的验证框架\n2. **扩展性受限**：添加新字段或自定义元数据需要修改核心模型\n3. **状态管理不清晰**：元数据中的状态字段（如 `agent_id`, `k8s_deployment`）缺乏明确的状态机\n4. **向后兼容性**：元数据格式变更可能导致兼容性问题\n5. **多环境支持**：缺乏对不同部署环境（开发、测试、生产）的元数据隔离\n\n## 当前实现分析\n\n### MetadataService 现状\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n```\n\n### AgentMetadata 模型现状\n\n当前包含以下主要字段：\n- 基本信息：`agent_name`, `description`, `language`\n- 运行时配置：`entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`\n- 部署信息：`region`, `version`, `image`\n- 认证信息：`auth`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`\n- Kubernetes 集成：`k8s_deployment`, `agent_id`\n- URL 配置：`agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`\n- 探针配置：`readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n\n## 问题陈述\n\n### 1. 验证逻辑分散\n\n当前的验证逻辑分散在多个地方：\n- Pydantic 模型中的验证器\n- MetadataService 中的验证方法\n- Runtime 类中的验证调用\n\n这导致：\n- 难以维护和调试\n- 验证规则不一致\n- 错误信息不统一\n\n### 2. 状态管理混乱\n\n元数据包含多种状态字段：\n- `agent_id`: AgentCube 分配的 ID\n- `version`: 语义版本\n- `k8s_deployment`: Kubernetes 部署信息\n- `session_id`: 会话 ID\n\n这些字段之间缺乏明确的状态转换规则和依赖关系。\n\n### 3. 扩展性不足\n\n当需要添加新的元数据字段时，必须修改核心模型，这可能导致：\n- 破坏向后兼容性\n- 增加核心模型的复杂度\n- 难以支持插件化的扩展\n\n### 4. 配置管理复杂\n\n不同环境（开发、测试、生产）需要不同的配置，但当前缺乏：\n- 环境配置隔离\n- 配置覆盖机制\n- 敏感信息保护\n\n## 提案方案\n\n### 1. 重构验证框架\n\n#### 1.1 统一验证器接口\n\n```python\nfrom abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n\nclass MetadataValidator(ABC):\n    \"\"\"元数据验证器基类\"\"\"\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> ValidationResult:\n        \"\"\"验证元数据并返回结果\"\"\"\n        pass\n\nclass ValidationResult:\n    \"\"\"验证结果\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, is_valid: bool, errors: List[str] = None, warnings: List[str] = None):\n        self.is_valid = is_valid\n        self.errors = errors or []\n        self.warnings = warnings or []\n    \n    def add_error(self, error: str) -> None:\n        self.errors.append(error)\n        self.is_valid = False\n    \n    def add_warning(self, warning: str) -> None:\n        self.warnings.append(warning)\n```\n\n#### 1.2 具体验证器实现\n\n```python\nclass BasicInfoValidator(MetadataValidator):\n    \"\"\"基本信息验证器\"\"\"\n    \n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> ValidationResult:\n        result = ValidationResult(is_valid=True)\n        \n        if not metadata.agent_name or len(metadata.agent_name) < 2:\n            result.add_error(\"agent_name must be at least 2 characters\")\n        \n        if metadata.language not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n            result.add_error(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n        \n        if not (1 <= metadata.port <= 65535):\n            result.add_error(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        \n        return result\n\nclass DeploymentValidator(MetadataValidator):\n    \"\"\"部署配置验证器\"\"\"\n    \n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> ValidationResult:\n        result = ValidationResult(is_valid=True)\n        \n        if metadata.build_mode not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n            result.add_error(f\"Invalid build_mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n        \n        if metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\" and not metadata.cloud_provider:\n            result.add_warning(\"cloud_provider is recommended for cloud builds\")\n        \n        return result\n\nclass KubernetesValidator(MetadataValidator):\n    \"\"\"Kubernetes 配置验证器\"\"\"\n    \n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> ValidationResult:\n        result = ValidationResult(is_valid=True)\n        \n        if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n            deployment = metadata.k8s_deployment\n            if deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n                if not metadata.router_url:\n                    result.add_error(\"router_url is required for AgentRuntime deployments\")\n                if not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n                    result.add_error(\"workload_manager_url is required for AgentRuntime deployments\")\n        \n        return result\n```\n\n#### 1.3 验证链模式\n\n```python\nclass MetadataValidationChain:\n    \"\"\"元数据验证链\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self):\n        self.validators: List[MetadataValidator] = []\n        self.add_default_validators()\n    \n    def add_default_validators(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"添加默认验证器\"\"\"\n        self.validators.extend([\n            BasicInfoValidator(),\n            DeploymentValidator(),\n            KubernetesValidator(),\n            WorkspaceValidator(),\n        ])\n    \n    def add_validator(self, validator: MetadataValidator) -> None:\n        \"\"\"添加自定义验证器\"\"\"\n        self.validators.append(validator)\n    \n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> ValidationResult:\n        \"\"\"执行所有验证\"\"\"\n        final_result = ValidationResult(is_valid=True)\n        \n        for validator in self.validators:\n            result = validator.validate(metadata)\n            final_result.errors.extend(result.errors)\n            final_result.warnings.extend(result.warnings)\n            if not result.is_valid:\n                final_result.is_valid = False\n        \n        return final_result\n```\n\n### 2. 状态机管理\n\n#### 2.1 定义状态模型\n\n```python\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass AgentState(str, Enum):\n    \"\"\"代理状态\"\"\"\n    UNINITIALIZED = \"uninitialized\"\n    PACKAGED = \"packaged\"\n    BUILT = \"built\"\n    PUBLISHED = \"published\"\n    RUNNING = \"running\"\n    STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n    ERROR = \"error\"\n\nclass AgentStateMachine:\n    \"\"\"代理状态机\"\"\"\n    \n    # 定义状态转换\n    TRANSITIONS = {\n        AgentState.UNINITIALIZED: [AgentState.PACKAGED],\n        AgentState.PACKAGED: [AgentState.BUILT],\n        AgentState.BUILT: [AgentState.PUBLISHED, AgentState.ERROR],\n        AgentState.PUBLISHED: [AgentState.RUNNING, AgentState.ERROR],\n        AgentState.RUNNING: [AgentState.STOPPED, AgentState.ERROR],\n        AgentState.STOPPED: [AgentState.RUNNING],\n        AgentState.ERROR: [AgentState.PACKAGED, AgentState.BUILT],\n    }\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def can_transition(cls, from_state: AgentState, to_state: AgentState) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"检查状态转换是否允许\"\"\"\n        return to_state in cls.TRANSITIONS.get(from_state, [])\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def validate_transition(cls, from_state: AgentState, to_state: AgentState) -> None:\n        \"\"\"验证状态转换，如果不允许则抛出异常\"\"\"\n        if not cls.can_transition(from_state, to_state):\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"Invalid state transition from {from_state} to {to_state}. \"\n                f\"Allowed transitions: {cls.TRANSITIONS.get(from_state, [])}\"\n            )\n```\n\n#### 2.2 扩展元数据模型\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"增强的代理元数据模型\"\"\"\n    \n    # ... 现有字段 ...\n    \n    # 新增状态管理字段\n    state: AgentState = AgentState.UNINITIALIZED\n    state_transitions: List[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    \n    # 新增时间戳\n    created_at: Optional[datetime] = None\n    updated_at: Optional[datetime] = None\n    \n    # 新增环境配置\n    environment: str = \"development\"  # development, testing, production\n    environment_overrides: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    \n    def transition_to(self, new_state: AgentState) -> None:\n        \"\"\"执行状态转换\"\"\"\n        AgentStateMachine.validate_transition(self.state, new_state)\n        \n        # 记录状态转换\n        self.state_transitions.append({\n            \"from\": self.state,\n            \"to\": new_state,\n            \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        })\n        \n        self.state = new_state\n        self.updated_at = datetime.utcnow()\n    \n    def get_effective_config(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"获取有效的配置（应用环境覆盖）\"\"\"\n        base_config = self.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n        base_config.pop(\"environment_overrides\", None)\n        base_config.pop(\"state_transitions\", None)\n        \n        # 应用环境覆盖\n        overrides = self.environment_overrides.get(self.environment, {})\n        return {**base_config, **overrides}\n```\n\n### 3. 扩展性增强\n\n#### 3.1 自定义元数据支持\n\n```python\nclass CustomMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"自定义元数据扩展\"\"\"\n    \n    custom_fields: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    \n    def get_field(self, key: str, default: Any = None) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"获取自定义字段\"\"\"\n        return self.custom_fields.get(key, default)\n    \n    def set_field(self, key: str, value: Any) -> None:\n        \"\"\"设置自定义字段\"\"\"\n        self.custom_fields[key] = value\n    \n    def remove_field(self, key: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"移除自定义字段\"\"\"\n        self.custom_fields.pop(key, None)\n\n# 扩展 AgentMetadata\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    # ... 现有字段 ...\n    custom_metadata: Optional[CustomMetadata] = None\n```\n\n#### 3.2 插件系统\n\n```python\nclass MetadataPlugin(ABC):\n    \"\"\"元数据插件基类\"\"\"\n    \n    @property\n    @abstractmethod\n    def name(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"插件名称\"\"\"\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def before_save(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"保存前的钩子\"\"\"\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def after_load(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"加载后的钩子\"\"\"\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> List[str]:\n        \"\"\"验证元数据，返回错误列表\"\"\"\n        pass\n\nclass MetadataPluginManager:\n    \"\"\"元数据插件管理器\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self):\n        self.plugins: List[MetadataPlugin] = []\n    \n    def register_plugin(self, plugin: MetadataPlugin) -> None:\n        \"\"\"注册插件\"\"\"\n        self.plugins.append(plugin)\n    \n    def unregister_plugin(self, plugin_name: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"注销插件\"\"\"\n        self.plugins = [p for p in self.plugins if p.name != plugin_name]\n    \n    def before_save(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"执行所有插件的保存前钩子\"\"\"\n        for plugin in self.plugins:\n            plugin.before_save(metadata)\n    \n    def after_load(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"执行所有插件的加载后钩子\"\"\"\n        for plugin in self.plugins:\n            plugin.after_load(metadata)\n    \n    def validate(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> List[str]:\n        \"\"\"执行所有插件的验证\"\"\"\n        all_errors = []\n        for plugin in self.plugins:\n            errors = plugin.validate(metadata)\n            all_errors.extend(errors)\n        return all_errors\n```\n\n### 4. 配置管理增强\n\n#### 4.1 多环境配置\n\n```python\nclass EnvironmentConfig(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"环境配置\"\"\"\n    \n    name: str\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = None\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = None\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = None\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    namespace: str = \"default\"\n    replicas: int = 1\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_dict(cls, env_name: str, config: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"EnvironmentConfig\":\n        \"\"\"从字典创建环境配置\"\"\"\n        return cls(name=env_name, **config)\n\nclass ConfigManager:\n    \"\"\"配置管理器\"\"\"\n    \n    DEFAULT_ENVIRONMENTS = {\n        \"development\": {\n            \"registry_url\": \"localhost:5000\",\n            \"namespace\": \"dev\",\n        },\n        \"testing\": {\n            \"namespace\": \"test\",\n        },\n        \"production\": {\n            \"replicas\": 3,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    def __init__(self, config_path: Optional[Path] = None):\n        self.environments: Dict[str, EnvironmentConfig] = {}\n        self._load_default_environments()\n        if config_path:\n            self._load_from_file(config_path)\n    \n    def _load_default_environments(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"加载默认环境配置\"\"\"\n        for env_name, config in self.DEFAULT_ENVIRONMENTS.items():\n            self.environments[env_name] = EnvironmentConfig.from_dict(env_name, config)\n    \n    def _load_from_file(self, config_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"从文件加载环境配置\"\"\"\n        if config_path.exists():\n            import yaml\n            with open(config_path, \"r\") as f:\n                config_data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n                for env_name, env_config in config_data.get(\"environments\", {}).items():\n                    self.environments[env_name] = EnvironmentConfig.from_dict(env_name, env_config)\n    \n    def get_environment(self, env_name: str) -> EnvironmentConfig:\n        \"\"\"获取环境配置\"\"\"\n        if env_name not in self.environments:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Environment not found: {env_name}\")\n        return self.environments[env_name]\n    \n    def apply_environment_config(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, env_name: str) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"应用环境配置到元数据\"\"\"\n        env_config = self.get_environment(env_name)\n        \n        # 更新元数据字段\n        if env_config.registry_url:\n            metadata.registry_url = env_config.registry_url\n        if env_config.registry_username:\n            metadata.registry_username = env_config.registry_username\n        if env_config.registry_password:\n            metadata.registry_password = env_config.registry_password\n        if env_config.cloud_provider:\n            metadata.cloud_provider = env_config.cloud_provider\n        if env_config.region:\n            metadata.region = env_config.region\n        if env_config.workload_manager_url:\n            metadata.workload_manager_url = env_config.workload_manager_url\n        if env_config.router_url:\n            metadata.router_url = env_config.router_url\n        \n        metadata.environment = env_name\n        return metadata\n```\n\n#### 4.2 敏感信息保护\n\n```python\nfrom cryptography.fernet import Fernet\nimport base64\nimport os\n\nclass SensitiveDataManager:\n    \"\"\"敏感信息管理器\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, key: Optional[bytes] = None):\n        \"\"\"初始化加密管理器\n        \n        Args:\n            key: 加密密钥，如果为 None 则从环境变量获取或生成新密钥\n        \"\"\"\n        if key is None:\n            key = self._get_or_create_key()\n        self.cipher = Fernet(key)\n    \n    def _get_or_create_key(self) -> bytes:\n        \"\"\"获取或创建加密密钥\"\"\"\n        key_str = os.environ.get(\"AGENTCUBE_ENCRYPTION_KEY\")\n        if key_str:\n            return base64.urlsafe_b64decode(key_str.encode())\n        else:\n            key = Fernet.generate_key()\n            os.environ[\"AGENTCUBE_ENCRYPTION_KEY\"] = base64.urlsafe_b64encode(key).decode()\n            return key\n    \n    def encrypt(self, data: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"加密数据\"\"\"\n        encrypted = self.cipher.encrypt(data.encode())\n        return base64.urlsafe_b64encode(encrypted).decode()\n    \n    def decrypt(self, encrypted_data: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"解密数据\"\"\"\n        encrypted = base64.urlsafe_b64decode(encrypted_data.encode())\n        decrypted = self.cipher.decrypt(encrypted)\n        return decrypted.decode()\n    \n    def encrypt_field(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, field_name: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"加密元数据中的敏感字段\"\"\"\n        field_value = getattr(metadata, field_name, None)\n        if field_value:\n            setattr(metadata, field_name, self.encrypt(field_value))\n    \n    def decrypt_field(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, field_name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"解密元数据中的敏感字段\"\"\"\n        field_value = getattr(metadata, field_name, None)\n        if field_value:\n            return self.decrypt(field_value)\n        return \"\"\n```\n\n### 5. 重构后的 MetadataService\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    \"\"\"增强的元数据服务\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        config_manager: Optional[ConfigManager] = None,\n        plugin_manager: Optional[MetadataPluginManager] = None,\n        sensitive_data_manager: Optional[SensitiveDataManager] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.config_manager = config_manager or ConfigManager()\n        self.plugin_manager = plugin_manager or MetadataPluginManager()\n        self.sensitive_data_manager = sensitive_data_manager\n        self.validation_chain = MetadataValidationChain()\n        \n        self.logger = get_logger(self.__class__.__name__)\n    \n    def load_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        environment: Optional[str] = None,\n        decrypt_sensitive: bool = True,\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"加载元数据\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: 工作空间路径\n            environment: 环境名称，如果提供则应用环境配置\n            decrypt_sensitive: 是否解密敏感字段\n            \n        Returns:\n            AgentMetadata: 加载的元数据\n        \"\"\"\n        metadata_file = self._find_metadata_file(workspace_path)\n        \n        with open(metadata_file, \"r\") as f:\n            metadata_dict = yaml.safe_load(f)\n        \n        metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n        \n        # 解密敏感字段\n        if decrypt_sensitive and self.sensitive_data_manager:\n            for field in [\"registry_password\", \"image_password\"]:\n                encrypted_value = getattr(metadata, field, None)\n                if encrypted_value and encrypted_value.startswith(\"encrypted:\"):\n                    decrypted_value = self.sensitive_data_manager.decrypt(\n                        encrypted_value.replace(\"encrypted:\", \"\", 1)\n                    )\n                    setattr(metadata, field, decrypted_value)\n        \n        # 应用环境配置\n        if environment:\n            metadata = self.config_manager.apply_environment_config(metadata, environment)\n        \n        # 执行插件加载后钩子\n        self.plugin_manager.after_load(metadata)\n        \n        # 验证元数据\n        validation_result = self.validation_chain.validate(metadata)\n        if not validation_result.is_valid:\n            error_msg = \"Metadata validation failed:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(validation_result.errors)\n            self.logger.error(error_msg)\n            raise ValueError(error_msg)\n        \n        if validation_result.warnings:\n            self.logger.warning(\n                \"Metadata validation warnings:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(validation_result.warnings)\n            )\n        \n        return metadata\n    \n    def save_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        encrypt_sensitive: bool = True,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"保存元数据\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: 工作空间路径\n            metadata: 要保存的元数据\n            encrypt_sensitive: 是否加密敏感字段\n        \"\"\"\n        # 执行插件保存前钩子\n        self.plugin_manager.before_save(metadata)\n        \n        # 验证元数据\n        validation_result = self.validation_chain.validate(metadata)\n        if not validation_result.is_valid:\n            error_msg = \"Metadata validation failed:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(validation_result.errors)\n            raise ValueError(error_msg)\n        \n        # 加密敏感字段\n        if encrypt_sensitive and self.sensitive_data_manager:\n            for field in [\"registry_password\", \"image_password\"]:\n                field_value = getattr(metadata, field, None)\n                if field_value and not field_value.startswith(\"encrypted:\"):\n                    encrypted_value = self.sensitive_data_manager.encrypt(field_value)\n                    setattr(metadata, field, f\"encrypted:{encrypted_value}\")\n        \n        # 更新时间戳\n        if metadata.created_at is None:\n            metadata.created_at = datetime.utcnow()\n        metadata.updated_at = datetime.utcnow()\n        \n        # 保存到文件\n        metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n        \n        with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n            yaml.dump(metadata_dict, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n        \n        self.logger.info(f\"Metadata saved to {metadata_file}\")\n    \n    def update_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        updates: Dict[str, Any],\n        transition_to: Optional[AgentState] = None,\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"更新元数据\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: 工作空间路径\n            updates: 更新内容的字典\n            transition_to: 可选的状态转换\n            \n        Returns:\n            AgentMetadata: 更新后的元数据\n        \"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        # 应用更新\n        for key, value in updates.items():\n            if hasattr(metadata, key):\n                setattr(metadata, key, value)\n        \n        # 执行状态转换\n        if transition_to:\n            metadata.transition_to(transition_to)\n        \n        # 保存更新后的元数据\n        self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        return metadata\n    \n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"验证工作空间\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: 工作空间路径\n            \n        Returns:\n            bool: 验证是否通过\n        \"\"\"\n        if not workspace_path.exists() or not workspace_path.is_dir():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        # 尝试加载元数据\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        # 根据语言验证工作空间结构\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        return True\n    \n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"验证 Python 工作空间\"\"\"\n        python_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not python_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n        \n        requirements_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n        if not (workspace_path / requirements_file).exists():\n            self.logger.warning(f\"Requirements file not found: {requirements_file}\")\n    \n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"验证 Java 工作空间\"\"\"\n        if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n    \n    def _find_metadata_file(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Path:\n        \"\"\"查找元数据文件\"\"\"\n        for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n            metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n            if metadata_file.exists():\n                return metadata_file\n        \n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}\")\n```\n\n## 实施计划\n\n### 阶段一：基础框架重构（2周）\n\n**目标**：建立新的验证框架和状态机\n\n**任务**：\n1. 实现 `MetadataValidator` 基类和验证器接口\n2. 实现状态机 `AgentStateMachine`\n3. 重构现有的验证逻辑到新的验证器\n4. 添加单元测试覆盖验证框架\n\n**交付物**：\n- 新的验证框架代码\n- 状态机实现\n- 单元测试覆盖率 > 80%\n\n### 阶段二：扩展性增强（1周）\n\n**目标**：实现插件系统和自定义元数据支持\n\n**任务**：\n1. 实现 `MetadataPlugin` 基类和插件管理器\n2. 扩展 `AgentMetadata` 支持自定义字段\n3. 实现示例插件（如版本检查、依赖验证）\n4. 编写插件开发文档\n\n**交付物**：\n- 插件系统代码\n- 示例插件\n- 插件开发文档\n\n### 阶段三：配置管理优化（1周）\n\n**目标**：实现多环境配置和敏感信息保护\n\n**任务**：\n1. 实现 `ConfigManager` 和环境配置\n2. 实现 `SensitiveDataManager` 和加密功能\n3. 更新 `MetadataService` 集成新功能\n4. 编写配置管理文档\n\n**交付物**：\n- 配置管理代码\n- 加密管理代码\n- 配置管理文档\n\n### 阶段四：集成和测试（1周）\n\n**目标**：全面集成新功能并进行测试\n\n**任务**：\n1. 更新所有 Runtime 类使用新的 MetadataService\n2. 编写集成测试\n3. 迁移现有测试用例\n4. 性能测试和优化\n\n**交付物**：\n- 更新的所有 Runtime 类\n- 集成测试套件\n- 性能测试报告\n\n### 阶段五：文档和发布（1周）\n\n**目标**：完善文档并准备发布\n\n**任务**：\n1. 更新 API 文档\n2. 编写迁移指南\n3. 编写用户指南\n4. 准备版本发布\n\n**交付物**：\n- 完整的 API 文档\n- 迁移指南\n- 用户指南\n- 版本发布说明\n\n## 影响分析\n\n### 向后兼容性\n\n**兼容性保证**：\n- 保留所有现有字段和方法\n- 元数据文件格式向后兼容\n- 旧的验证逻辑逐步迁移\n\n**迁移策略**：\n1. 保留旧的验证逻辑作为兼容层\n2. 新功能通过配置开关控制\n3. 提供迁移脚本转换旧元数据\n\n### 性能影响\n\n**预期影响**：\n- 验证框架：轻微性能提升（优化验证逻辑）\n- 加密功能：密码操作增加 10-20ms 延迟\n- 插件系统：根据插件数量线性增加\n\n**优化措施**：\n- 延迟加载插件\n- 加密操作异步化\n- 缓存验证结果\n\n### 依赖变更\n\n**新增依赖**：\n- `cryptography`（用于加密功能）\n\n**版本要求**：\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0`（保持不变）\n- `pyyaml>=6.0`（保持不变）\n\n## 风险评估\n\n### 高风险\n\n1. **状态转换兼容性**\n   - 风险：现有代码依赖隐式状态转换\n   - 缓解：保留兼容层，详细日志记录\n\n2. **加密密钥管理**\n   - 风险：密钥丢失导致数据无法解密\n   - 缓解：提供密钥备份和恢复机制\n\n### 中风险\n\n1. **插件生态系统**\n   - 风险：缺乏插件导致扩展能力未充分利用\n   - 缓解：提供核心插件集合和开发指南\n\n2. **性能回归**\n   - 风险：新功能影响 CLI 响应速度\n   - 缓解：性能测试和优化\n\n### 低风险\n\n1. **配置复杂性**\n   - 风险：多环境配置增加学习曲线\n   - 缓解：提供默认配置和详细文档\n\n## 成功指标\n\n### 技术指标\n\n- 单元测试覆盖率 > 85%\n- 集成测试覆盖率 > 70%\n- 验证响应时间 < 50ms\n- 加密操作延迟 < 20ms\n\n### 质量指标\n\n- 代码审查通过率 100%\n- 静态分析无严重问题\n- 文档完整性 > 90%\n\n### 用户体验指标\n\n- 元数据加载错误率降低 50%\n- 配置迁移成功率 > 95%\n- 用户满意度调查 > 8/10\n\n## 备选方案\n\n### 方案 A：最小化改动\n\n**描述**：仅重构验证逻辑，保持其他功能不变\n\n**优点**：\n- 改动范围小\n- 风险低\n- 实施快速\n\n**缺点**：\n- 不解决扩展性问题\n- 状态管理仍然混乱\n- 配置管理未改善\n\n### 方案 B：激进重构\n\n**描述**：完全重写元数据系统，采用新的数据模型\n\n**优点**：\n- 彻底解决现有问题\n- 更好的架构设计\n- 长期维护成本低\n\n**缺点**：\n- 实施周期长\n- 兼容性挑战大\n- 风险高\n\n### 推荐方案：渐进式增强\n\n采用本提案的方案，通过分阶段实施，在保证兼容性的同时逐步增强功能。\n\n## 结论\n\n本提案通过引入统一的验证框架、状态机管理、插件系统和配置管理增强，显著改善了 MetadataService 和数据模型的架构。该方案在保持向后兼容性的同时，提供了更好的扩展性、可维护性和用户体验。\n\n建议按照实施计划分阶段推进，每个阶段都有明确的交付物和验证标准，确保项目质量和进度可控。","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871995922,"end":1775871996059}}}}
